        "TileImage": "$($repository f559fd89-0c3f-4e8c-aa84-a9de98b0f9d3).Image",
        "Description": "Bob the Builder rose to power in Builderland, fixing its economy as a democratic leader. Frustrated by parliament&apos;s inefficiency, he exploited a crisis, gaining emergency powers to &quot;streamline progress.&quot; Propaganda painted him as a unifying force, and his slogan, “Can we fix it? Yes we can!”, became a rallying cry for fascist ideals. Bob militarized the nation, silenced dissent, and built an empire. Builderland, once hopeful, was now a war machine under his iron rule.\r\rAlso he stole Böjti outfit",
